
@startuml

' Define the classes
class Department {
  +id: int
  +name: string
  +rooms: List<Room>
}

class Room {
  +id: int
  +number: string
  +department: Department
  +beds: List<Bed>
}

class Bed {
  +id: int
  +category: Category
  +room: Room
  +isOccupied: boolean
  +inhabitant: Inhabitant (0..1)
}

class Category {
  +id: int
  +type: string (e.g., RH, RNH, SF)
  +price: decimal
}

class Inhabitant {
  +id: int
  +name: string
  +registrationDate: Date
  +waitingListPosition: int
  +stays: List<Stay>
  +assessmentResults: List<Assessment>
}

class Stay {
  +id: int
  +startDate: Date
  +endDate: Date
  +category: Category
  +bed: Bed
  +isSuspended: boolean
  +invoice: Invoice
}

class Assessment {
  +id: int
  +date: Date
  +results: Map<string, string>
  +inhabitant: Inhabitant
}

class Proposal {
  +id: int
  +date: Date
  +category: Category
  +inhabitant: Inhabitant
  +status: string (e.g., pending, accepted, refused)
}

class Invoice {
  +id: int
  +issueDate: Date
  +dueDate: Date
  +amount: decimal
  +outstandingAmount: decimal
  +stay: Stay
  +status: string (e.g., pending, paid, partially paid)
}

class Payment {
  +id: int
  +date: Date
  +amount: decimal
  +invoice: Invoice
  +isRefund: boolean
}

' Associations

Department "1" -- "0..*" Room : contains
Room "1" -- "0..*" Bed : has
Bed "1" -- "0..1" Inhabitant : assigned to
Category "1" -- "0..*" Bed : defines
Inhabitant "1" -- "0..*" Stay : has
Stay "1" -- "1" Category : of type
Stay "1" -- "1" Bed : uses
Inhabitant "1" -- "0..*" Assessment : has
Inhabitant "1" -- "0..*" Proposal : is proposed to
Proposal "1" -- "1" Category : for
Proposal "1" -- "1" Inhabitant : for
Stay "1" -- "1" Invoice : generates
Invoice "1" -- "0..*" Payment : has

@enduml

### Notes:
- **Inheritance**: There is no explicit inheritance in this model, but `Stay` could potentially be extended if different types of stays had unique behavior.
- **Associations**: Relationships between objects are clearly defined with direction and multiplicity.
- **State/Status**: Status attributes like `isSuspended`, `status`, and `status` are included where relevant to capture the dynamic aspects of the system.

